00:30.701 --> 00:32.317
You're tipping your shoulder
before you throw the right.

00:32.317 --> 00:33.834
The hell I am.

00:39.742 --> 00:41.808
- When's tip-off?
- Eight.

00:41.833 --> 00:43.518
That's your pre-game?
That place's a rip-off.

00:43.518 --> 00:45.450
I'm not spending eight
bucks on a beer.

00:45.450 --> 00:46.463
I got a shift in the morning,

00:46.488 --> 00:47.761
so we should probably
take it easy tonight.

00:47.761 --> 00:49.203
Yeah. All right.

00:49.690 --> 00:51.150
Where are the seats?

00:51.770 --> 00:54.419
- They're ain't court-side.
- [INDISTINCT]

00:56.098 --> 00:58.345
I was your C.O.
We did two tours together.

00:58.371 --> 00:59.775
Hell, I took a bullet for you!

00:59.800 --> 01:01.523
You oughta know me better than that.

01:07.043 --> 01:08.219
There!

01:08.244 --> 01:09.508
You did it again!

01:10.180 --> 01:12.145
There's a place over on Franklin.

01:12.145 --> 01:13.883
Three dollar draft.
Pretty decent wings.

01:13.883 --> 01:15.265
That place is a dump.

01:15.290 --> 01:18.215
Yeah, I'm not exactly swimming
in EMT money, all right?

01:18.240 --> 01:21.335
My job at the VA barely covers my tab.

01:21.519 --> 01:22.767
I'm telling you,
you're tipping your strike.

01:22.792 --> 01:24.394
I can see it coming a mile away.

01:28.128 --> 01:30.155
Did you see that one?

01:31.095 --> 01:32.193
Nope.

01:39.561 --> 01:42.036
- You still hit like a girl.
- There's nothing wrong with that.

01:44.614 --> 01:45.642
Cool.

01:45.642 --> 01:47.152
You're done?

01:47.850 --> 01:50.594
I'm not the one getting my ass kicked.

02:11.835 --> 02:13.614
I taught you that.

02:13.678 --> 02:14.907
I know.

02:14.993 --> 02:17.498
All right. Come on.
We're gonna be late.

02:17.498 --> 02:18.971
Coffee's on you.

02:19.752 --> 02:21.641
What else is new?

02:26.896 --> 02:28.210
<i>Good morning, Portland!</i>

02:28.210 --> 02:32.020
<i>We start the hour with an update
from the Horace Hayes trial. Kelly?</i>

02:32.192 --> 02:33.888
<i>Yes, good morning, Tom.</i>

02:33.888 --> 02:36.634
<i>Well, there certainly is a
nervous energy in the air today</i>

02:36.634 --> 02:39.341
<i>with closing arguments being read
in the Horace Hayes trial...</i>

02:39.341 --> 02:41.721
<i>and deliberations set to
begin this afternoon.</i>

02:41.769 --> 02:43.672
<i>Well, many members
of the community</i>

02:43.672 --> 02:47.146
<i>fear another hung jury and the
possibility of Hayes walking free.</i>

02:47.174 --> 02:49.470
<i>The prosecution certainly
seemed confident</i>

02:49.495 --> 02:51.189
<i>as they convened in the hallway.</i>

02:51.214 --> 02:54.783
<i>And any updates on the rest of
the alleged Irish crime family?</i>

02:54.808 --> 02:56.838
<i>Yes, they pressed
the District Attorney to...</i>

02:56.838 --> 02:58.668
[PHONE RINGS]

03:00.101 --> 03:02.908
- Hey!
<i>- Yo, when's your Dad back?</i>

03:02.933 --> 03:05.086
I don't know.
Whenever they reach a verdict.

03:05.111 --> 03:07.907
<i>So, you've got the house
to yourself tomorrow night?</i>

03:07.932 --> 03:11.333
Yeah... but no, not gonna happen.

03:11.333 --> 03:13.543
<i>- What?</i>
- You know what!

03:13.591 --> 03:15.971
- I'm not having people over.
<i>- Why not?</i>

03:16.036 --> 03:19.382
- We've got finals next week, for one...
<i>- What if I invited Andrew?</i>

03:19.390 --> 03:21.987
- My Dad would kill me!
<i>- He'll never know.</i>

03:22.012 --> 03:23.562
That's not the point.

03:23.587 --> 03:25.363
<i>We'll keep it low-key.</i>

03:25.828 --> 03:26.978
Okay, fine.

03:26.978 --> 03:29.796
But just a couple of people.
That's it. I'm serious.

03:29.864 --> 03:31.060
<i>Yes!</i>

03:31.579 --> 03:33.825
I'll see you at practice.

03:40.172 --> 03:41.612
Can I help you?

03:46.701 --> 03:48.263
Get in the car, Sarah.

03:48.263 --> 03:49.913
How do you know my name?

03:53.123 --> 03:54.639
Circle around!

04:07.621 --> 04:10.182
- Where the fuck did she go?
- That way. Go!

04:35.203 --> 04:36.998
Come on, Sarah.

04:40.199 --> 04:42.411
We're not gonna hurt you.

04:57.577 --> 04:59.006
Sarah!

05:02.812 --> 05:04.670
Sarah!

05:13.638 --> 05:15.522
Sarah!

05:35.440 --> 05:36.677
I got her, Maddy!

05:36.677 --> 05:38.111
Get off me!

05:39.103 --> 05:40.956
You should have got in the car.

05:46.070 --> 05:48.173
What do you want from me?

05:53.360 --> 05:54.638
Put him on.

05:54.685 --> 05:56.975
Someone wants to say hi.

05:57.291 --> 05:58.729
- Sarah!
<i>- Dad!</i>

05:58.729 --> 06:00.047
- Oh, my God! Sarah!
- Hey!

06:00.067 --> 06:01.313
<i>Dad!</i>

06:01.745 --> 06:04.844
<i>Patrick, your daughter's gonna be fine.</i>

06:04.938 --> 06:07.936
<i>We just need to talk
about my father's trial.</i>

06:08.545 --> 06:10.276
What do you want from me?

06:10.301 --> 06:12.242
You hang the Jury,

06:12.508 --> 06:14.677
or we'll hang your girl.

06:16.750 --> 06:18.421
Get her in the car.

06:35.102 --> 06:36.682
Thanks for coming out
with me today, man.

06:36.682 --> 06:38.587
- I appreciate it.
- No worries.

06:38.639 --> 06:39.976
It's not like it was
my day off or anything.

06:39.976 --> 06:42.094
Come on, you might as well
get out and help some people out.

06:42.119 --> 06:43.543
Yeah, yeah...
Happy to help.

06:43.568 --> 06:45.896
I just didn't know the old
DVA made house calls.

06:45.921 --> 06:46.900
Normally we don't.

06:46.925 --> 06:50.051
Usually they have got me sitting
behind a desk filing claims.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.002
Can't stand being in the office.

06:52.033 --> 06:53.281
But every now and then,

06:53.281 --> 06:54.849
they let me get out,
make a few rounds,

06:54.874 --> 06:56.404
check-in on some vets.

06:56.423 --> 06:57.776
I'm good with people.

06:57.801 --> 06:59.895
- So, who are we checking on today?
- Tommy.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.919
Nam vet, won a Purple Heart.

07:02.051 --> 07:03.755
Squatting in this
building for two years.

07:03.755 --> 07:05.046
Can't seem to get him out.

07:05.046 --> 07:06.262
Does he have any family?

07:06.266 --> 07:07.408
No, not anymore.

07:07.408 --> 07:09.554
I got a place set up
for him and everything, but...

07:09.625 --> 07:11.652
I can't get through to him.

07:11.838 --> 07:13.114
What makes you think
he'll listen to me?

07:13.140 --> 07:14.929
Remember a kid named Robert Walker?

07:14.942 --> 07:16.636
Served with you in Afghanistan?

07:16.694 --> 07:19.350
Yeah, Robbie,
the sniper attached to our unit.

07:19.375 --> 07:22.139
Killed by roadside just
outside of in Kabul. Why?

07:22.657 --> 07:24.343
He's his father.

07:28.924 --> 07:31.117
This place looks like a war zone.

07:31.194 --> 07:32.726
Wait til you see the inside.

07:32.759 --> 07:34.938
Oh, hey, and heads-up about Graham.

07:34.963 --> 07:37.113
He's a little touchy,
but he's all right.

07:37.138 --> 07:38.902
He works for the landlord.

07:41.625 --> 07:43.267
You're late!

07:43.343 --> 07:45.059
I've been waiting out here for an hour!

07:45.084 --> 07:47.188
It's nice to see you too, Graham.

07:47.213 --> 07:48.617
Fuck you!

07:50.094 --> 07:51.814
He seems nice.

08:09.422 --> 08:11.087
People actually live out here?

08:11.087 --> 08:14.372
Oh, yeah. This place is
a squatter's paradise.

08:14.397 --> 08:17.017
Nobody tells them what to do,
and they get to run the land.

08:17.037 --> 08:18.339
In the middle of nowhere.

08:18.339 --> 08:21.204
Yap. Old Tom likes living off the grid.

08:21.229 --> 08:22.685
What's in the bag?

08:22.892 --> 08:24.643
Just a little care package.

08:24.678 --> 08:27.159
Bread, ding-dong, stuff like that.

08:27.447 --> 08:28.653
Who's this guy?

08:28.694 --> 08:30.595
This is my buddy Jake.
He's helping me out today.

08:30.595 --> 08:31.786
How you doing?

08:31.846 --> 08:34.477
Huh? Terrible, I said I'm doing...
I said I'd help but...

08:34.477 --> 08:36.548
- I don't like sitting around all day.
- Take it easy, Graham.

08:36.548 --> 08:38.082
We're gonna be in and out.

08:38.107 --> 08:40.389
All right. Let's get it over with.

08:40.389 --> 08:41.975
This place gives me the creeps.

08:42.017 --> 08:45.193
Yeah, I'm surprised they let you
out here all by yourself today.

08:47.609 --> 08:48.716
I'm not worried.

08:48.716 --> 08:50.527
You got a permit for that thing?

08:50.527 --> 08:51.648
Of course!

08:51.673 --> 08:52.812
I got it last week.

08:52.837 --> 08:54.116
I hope you'll never need it.

08:54.116 --> 08:56.137
A lot better to have one
and not need it.

08:56.162 --> 08:58.474
- Than not to have one...
- Graham, do us a favor...

08:58.525 --> 09:00.183
Keep it in your pants, all right?

09:00.183 --> 09:02.648
Don't want you shooting me by accident.

09:25.077 --> 09:26.533
Ugh!

09:26.852 --> 09:28.753
It smells great in here.

09:28.961 --> 09:32.386
Man, it usually looks like
a hobo hotel in this place.

09:32.411 --> 09:34.026
Where is everybody?

09:34.174 --> 09:35.586
No clue.

09:35.611 --> 09:37.852
Say Graham, when was the last time
you were out here?

09:37.877 --> 09:39.616
A couple of months ago.

09:39.859 --> 09:41.877
Last time I let you in.

09:45.607 --> 09:47.307
Hello?

09:47.462 --> 09:49.099
Hello?

09:50.379 --> 09:52.161
Hello?

09:54.907 --> 09:58.403
Man, it looks like somebody cleared
the place and kicked everybody out.

09:58.428 --> 10:00.928
Maybe they all got jobs.

10:01.351 --> 10:03.242
It seems they left in a hurry.

10:03.276 --> 10:04.767
They didn't even finish their dinner.

10:04.811 --> 10:06.450
It wasn't us.
You know, it's not worth the trouble.

10:06.450 --> 10:08.506
We kick them out, they come back.
We kick them out, they come back.

10:08.506 --> 10:10.408
Like a pack of strays.

10:10.546 --> 10:12.471
They're human beings.

10:12.555 --> 10:15.167
- Yeah, right...
- Hey!

10:15.259 --> 10:17.907
If you don't care about this people,
then why are you still here?

10:17.932 --> 10:19.612
We're big boys.
We'll be all right.

10:19.637 --> 10:22.302
No, no, that's not how it works.
I let you in, I let you out.

10:22.302 --> 10:25.488
- We don't a lawsuit...
- Look, you two, cut it out.

10:25.648 --> 10:27.937
All right?
We're on the same team.

10:46.703 --> 10:49.043
- Are you sure he's still here?
- I hope so.

10:49.130 --> 10:51.132
He lives in a storeroom at the back.

10:51.158 --> 10:53.081
How did you find this
guy in the first place?

10:53.106 --> 10:54.737
Graham called it in.

10:54.762 --> 10:57.047
He may be an asshole,
but he's not a monster.

10:57.072 --> 10:58.782
Thank you.

11:01.098 --> 11:03.872
Easy there, Rambo,
it's a raccoon.

11:03.904 --> 11:05.903
Graham, what did I say?
That things isn't a toy!

11:05.928 --> 11:07.551
- No, but I saw...
- Look...

11:07.576 --> 11:10.189
You pull the piece again,
I'm gonna make you eat it.

11:10.210 --> 11:12.529
- We understand each other?
- Yeah, yeah, I got it.

11:27.630 --> 11:29.625
Tommy, open up!

11:30.313 --> 11:32.441
Tommy, it's Luke!

11:33.098 --> 11:35.134
Come on, Tommy.

11:36.146 --> 11:37.889
All right. We're coming in.

11:37.904 --> 11:39.699
Hope you're decent!

11:40.011 --> 11:42.141
Whoa! Whoa, whoa!

11:42.479 --> 11:45.045
You ain't coming inside of nothing.

11:45.412 --> 11:47.067
This is my home.

11:47.092 --> 11:49.425
That's fine.
Take it easy.

11:49.883 --> 11:52.125
I already told you I ain't going.

11:52.221 --> 11:54.359
You hear me?
I ain't going!

11:55.344 --> 11:57.440
- You got something to say to me?
- No, no, no!

11:57.445 --> 11:59.892
Not me. You can stay here
for as long as you like.

11:59.894 --> 12:01.861
Tommy, look,
I don't know what you're talking about.

12:01.861 --> 12:05.358
It's me, Luke, from the VA,
we spoke last month.

12:06.633 --> 12:08.054
I'm still not leaving.

12:08.079 --> 12:11.799
That's fine. Why don't you
put that thing down? Okay?

12:11.799 --> 12:14.435
Please. Put it down.

12:16.726 --> 12:18.434
It ain't even loaded.

12:18.459 --> 12:21.044
Maybe you shouldn't go
pointing at people's faces.

12:21.069 --> 12:22.904
This is America, isn't it?

12:23.728 --> 12:25.858
I just wanted to check
and see how you're doing.

12:25.883 --> 12:27.495
I brought you some food.

12:33.716 --> 12:36.085
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm Jake Carter.

12:36.096 --> 12:37.916
Is that supposed
to mean something to me?

12:41.930 --> 12:44.435
I served with your son in Afghanistan.

12:46.773 --> 12:48.304
Robbie?

12:48.806 --> 12:50.973
He was attached to my unit.

12:52.251 --> 12:53.806
Oh...

12:54.420 --> 12:56.153
He was a good boy.

12:56.391 --> 12:58.088
He was a good Marine.

12:59.522 --> 13:01.618
They brought him home in a box!

13:02.155 --> 13:03.636
Look, Tommy,

13:03.778 --> 13:05.668
why don't we sit down
for a second and talk?

13:05.668 --> 13:07.093
No, I don't think so.

13:07.127 --> 13:08.402
Come on, man,
we're just trying to help.

13:08.427 --> 13:10.122
Can't help. No one can help me.

13:10.147 --> 13:13.118
Just leave me be.

13:13.699 --> 13:16.640
I've asked you twice.
I won't ask you again.

13:20.658 --> 13:22.413
That went well.

13:22.804 --> 13:25.459
- Well, at least he didn't shoot us.
- Yeah.

13:25.484 --> 13:27.131
That's a plus.

13:30.182 --> 13:33.042
Oh, I gotta take this.

13:33.067 --> 13:36.139
Okay, come on. Time's up. Let's go.

13:36.356 --> 13:39.323
Yeah, I'll catch up with you.

13:39.348 --> 13:40.554
Hi!

13:41.936 --> 13:43.645
Yeah, this is he.

13:44.269 --> 13:45.605
Great.

13:49.200 --> 13:50.459
You're all right?

13:50.470 --> 13:52.305
Yeah, I just thought
we had him for a second.

13:52.339 --> 13:55.012
- We can't save everyone, brother.
- We can try.

13:55.037 --> 13:57.364
"No man left behind," right?
That's what they taught us.

13:57.410 --> 13:59.029
We're not in the war anymore, man.

13:59.054 --> 13:59.970
I'm still a Marine.

13:59.970 --> 14:02.329
- [GIRL SCREAMING]
- Come here!

14:02.343 --> 14:04.073
What's upstairs?

14:04.190 --> 14:06.069
Old office space.

14:06.094 --> 14:09.616
They usually don't squat upstairs
'cause the ceiling is leaking.

14:12.067 --> 14:13.945
All right. Let's go.

14:15.073 --> 14:16.854
Hi, yeah, listen...

14:36.418 --> 14:38.348
Yeah, send them over,

14:38.348 --> 14:40.394
and then I can...
I'll pull them off...

14:40.394 --> 14:42.302
I'm sure... yeah,
we can come up with a deal

14:42.327 --> 14:44.059
that's gonna be advantageous
for the both of us.

14:44.090 --> 14:46.315
So, that's gonna be...
That's gonna be great!

14:49.141 --> 14:50.618
Where do you wanna start?

14:50.618 --> 14:52.658
[GIRL GAGGING]

14:55.531 --> 14:56.734
Hey!

14:57.328 --> 14:59.039
Is everything all right in there?

14:59.064 --> 15:00.702
Freeze!

15:01.156 --> 15:03.494
Come on, we know you're in there.
We can hear you!

15:06.747 --> 15:08.941
Just wanna make sure
everything's all right.

15:12.281 --> 15:13.385
What do you think?

15:13.410 --> 15:14.892
Maybe Graham has a key?

15:16.349 --> 15:17.116
[HELP!]

15:17.141 --> 15:19.413
[YOU DO THAT AGAIN AND I WILL KILL YOU]

15:19.438 --> 15:20.810
You're up.

15:29.031 --> 15:30.237
It figures.

15:30.266 --> 15:32.497
- Can I help you?
- You know what?

15:32.497 --> 15:33.932
We can see you're all eating dinner.

15:33.932 --> 15:35.126
We're interrupting,
so, we're gonna...

15:35.151 --> 15:36.320
Are you okay?

15:36.345 --> 15:38.988
She's fine.
We just had a little disagreement.

15:39.251 --> 15:41.111
I'd like to hear it from her,
if you don't mind.

15:41.111 --> 15:42.325
Why not?

15:42.562 --> 15:44.395
Tell them, Sarah.

15:47.750 --> 15:50.313
- I'm fine.
- See? She's fine.

15:51.293 --> 15:53.489
Maybe we should call the police,
let them sort this out.

15:53.489 --> 15:55.638
- Oh, that won't be necessary.
- I insist.

15:55.638 --> 15:57.198
[COCKS GUN]

15:57.593 --> 15:59.614
There's no need for the police, Jake.

15:59.662 --> 16:02.162
Maybe we should just be on our way out.

16:02.918 --> 16:04.340
Unbelievable.

16:04.808 --> 16:05.576
Move!

16:05.601 --> 16:08.493
- Take it easy! All right!
- Just stay calm.

16:10.768 --> 16:11.978
Hey!

16:13.653 --> 16:15.579
You won't be needing this.

16:15.992 --> 16:17.354
Search them.

16:25.668 --> 16:28.285
Let's see who we're dealing with here.

16:32.413 --> 16:35.472
"Luke Trapper, Veteran Affairs."

16:35.497 --> 16:37.352
How noble of you.

16:37.657 --> 16:39.975
"Jake Carter, EMT."

16:40.002 --> 16:42.778
Oh, won't you look at that!
Both of you are soldiers.

16:42.803 --> 16:45.141
- How cute.
- Marines.

16:45.949 --> 16:47.411
Marines.

16:47.411 --> 16:49.625
Is that why you're out
here kicking down doors?

16:49.645 --> 16:51.479
Trying to relive your glory days?

16:51.504 --> 16:52.497
Something like that.

16:52.497 --> 16:55.149
Well, you took the gun on
this one, didn't you, chap?

16:55.427 --> 16:58.009
You guys ready?
I wanna get out of here bef...

17:01.891 --> 17:03.839
- Don't move!
- Whoa! Whoa!

17:03.864 --> 17:05.798
- Whoa!
- Graham, put that thing away.

17:05.823 --> 17:07.272
You're gonna get us all killed.

17:07.363 --> 17:09.441
Listen to your friend, okay?

17:09.464 --> 17:10.661
I said don't move!

17:10.661 --> 17:12.310
Just let them go, please.

17:12.335 --> 17:14.075
That ship has sailed, Sarah.

17:14.075 --> 17:16.409
You should've kept your mouth shut.

17:16.434 --> 17:18.631
Have you ever shot that gun before?

17:18.730 --> 17:20.130
Stop, please.

17:20.209 --> 17:22.510
'Cause it's got one hell of a kick.

17:22.535 --> 17:23.888
Stop talking.

17:23.888 --> 17:25.164
Plus...

17:25.560 --> 17:27.672
You left the safety on.

17:29.052 --> 17:31.443
[SCREAMS FRANTICALLY]

17:35.992 --> 17:37.332
Luke!

17:49.312 --> 17:51.136
- Come on!
- Move it!

18:02.423 --> 18:04.327
- What was that, Jake?
- No clue!

18:04.327 --> 18:06.143
Shit, we're trapped in here!

18:06.265 --> 18:08.195
- Are you all right?
- No, no, no, no...

18:08.195 --> 18:10.032
Hey, hey, hey, hey...

18:10.126 --> 18:11.597
Look at me. Look at me.

18:11.597 --> 18:13.272
- They're gonna kill us.
- No, they're not.

18:13.272 --> 18:15.264
We're not gonna let that
happen, are we, Luke?

18:15.289 --> 18:17.422
Probably not.

18:17.422 --> 18:18.965
Come on!

18:20.057 --> 18:22.729
- What's your name?
- Sarah.

18:22.738 --> 18:25.302
Right, Sarah.
We're gonna get you out of here.

18:25.583 --> 18:27.223
You believe me, right?

18:33.382 --> 18:35.326
- Yeah.
- Then say it.

18:35.663 --> 18:37.794
You're gonna get me out of here.

18:38.087 --> 18:40.085
- That's right.
- How?

18:40.165 --> 18:41.719
Still working on that.

18:41.744 --> 18:43.575
I need a little help over here.

18:47.451 --> 18:48.968
Never mind.
We're good.

18:52.018 --> 18:53.116
[GUNSHOT]

18:53.116 --> 18:54.655
Shit! Come on!
Move it over here!

18:54.655 --> 18:57.333
Come here, come here!
Get over here!

18:57.412 --> 18:59.315
- What?
- We need her alive.

18:59.342 --> 19:01.575
- Yeah, I know that.
- Then, why are you shooting at them?

19:01.611 --> 19:03.160
He broke John's hand.

19:03.179 --> 19:05.172
I don't care about John's hand.

19:05.197 --> 19:07.041
No more guns.

19:07.083 --> 19:09.602
We can't risk hitting the girl.
Understood?

19:09.602 --> 19:11.383
Whatever you say, Maddy.

19:11.383 --> 19:13.853
Call my brother.
Tell him to bring the boys.

19:13.878 --> 19:16.182
Until my father's verdict is in,

19:16.182 --> 19:17.858
we can't take any chances.

19:17.858 --> 19:19.290
What about them?

19:21.808 --> 19:23.428
Guard the door.

19:23.523 --> 19:25.240
It's a dead end.

19:25.689 --> 19:28.326
- They're not going anywhere.
- Let's go!

19:30.566 --> 19:33.283
Here. Happy Birthday.

19:49.158 --> 19:52.287
<i>Ladies and Gentlemen of the Jury...</i>

19:52.350 --> 19:56.841
<i>you have witnessed ironclad
proof of Horace Hayes' guilt.</i>

19:56.866 --> 20:00.875
<i>We have indisputable scientific
evidence on the murder weapon,</i>

20:00.910 --> 20:04.275
<i>and CCTV images from
the night of March 4th,</i>

20:04.340 --> 20:07.873
<i>showing Horace Hayes and his
associates entering the building,</i>

20:07.873 --> 20:12.159
<i>where three of Portland's finest
police officers were slain.</i>

20:12.184 --> 20:14.523
<i>Men with families and children...</i>

20:14.523 --> 20:16.283
<i>And beyond that, we've unveiled</i>

20:16.283 --> 20:18.888
<i>an extremely dangerous
head of a crime family...</i>

20:18.888 --> 20:21.135
<i>with a far reach across the nation...</i>

20:21.190 --> 20:24.692
<i>To truly kill a snake,
you must cut off his head.</i>

20:24.694 --> 20:27.886
<i>Now, go do what is right.
Thank you, Your Honor.</i>

21:03.421 --> 21:07.453
[TOILET FLUSHING]

21:10.837 --> 21:13.091
[RESTROOM DOOR OPENS]

21:14.985 --> 21:18.887
[FOOTSTEPS]

21:23.152 --> 21:24.651
- Hey.
- Hey.

21:25.488 --> 21:27.935
Would you believe we're supposed
to deliberate this shit?

21:27.935 --> 21:31.011
This is some asshole, isn't he?
We're gonna find this guy guilty.

21:35.613 --> 21:38.046
- Wait, wait, Ben.
- Yeah?

21:40.334 --> 21:42.216
No, nothing.

21:54.262 --> 21:57.424
Okay. Deliberation room three.
Let's go.

22:32.415 --> 22:34.704
It's too high.
We got to find a way out of here.

22:34.704 --> 22:36.533
I'm working on it.

22:38.197 --> 22:39.968
We got company.

22:39.993 --> 22:41.522
A squad or a platoon?

22:41.547 --> 22:43.465
Looks like the whole division.

22:46.202 --> 22:49.157
Hey, Sarah, do you want to tell us
what these people want with you?

22:49.157 --> 22:51.919
My father's a Juror on
the Horace Hayes trial.

22:52.942 --> 22:54.371
They want to mistrial.

22:54.396 --> 22:56.175
They're using me as leverage.

22:56.200 --> 22:58.361
- The Hayes family?
- Yeah.

22:59.729 --> 23:01.867
This just keeps getting
better and better.

23:01.892 --> 23:04.254
[YO, WE'RE HERE]

23:04.286 --> 23:07.698
Hey, Oscar, we got two
Marines trapped up here.

23:07.723 --> 23:09.553
Clear the rest of the building.

23:09.591 --> 23:12.319
No one should be here
except for you guys.

23:20.502 --> 23:21.524
Hey!

23:21.570 --> 23:22.837
Scout out the building.

23:22.837 --> 23:25.414
Make sure there isn't any more
Marines wandering around.

23:25.414 --> 23:26.924
What are you talking about?

23:26.949 --> 23:28.606
Just do it.

23:31.504 --> 23:33.386
Marines?

24:38.914 --> 24:41.524
I'd stand back.
We wanna give the all clear.

24:41.550 --> 24:43.853
Oh, wait, where are you going?

24:44.234 --> 24:45.661
You're up.

24:52.143 --> 24:54.535
I'm gonna kick your ass, man!

24:57.370 --> 24:59.545
Maddy! They're over here!

25:10.942 --> 25:12.426
Over here!

25:35.037 --> 25:36.505
You good?

25:38.197 --> 25:39.385
Yeah.

25:40.776 --> 25:42.481
We need a phone.

25:45.950 --> 25:47.355
I got one.

25:47.380 --> 25:49.247
Pass code.

25:49.744 --> 25:52.184
- Come on.
- Don't lock it out.

25:52.425 --> 25:55.183
You can make an emergency
call from the lock screen.

25:55.190 --> 25:57.865
- I don't see it.
- Here, give it to me.

26:02.591 --> 26:05.486
- He must have blocked it.
- Mine too.

26:07.744 --> 26:09.644
We gotta keep moving.

26:10.672 --> 26:11.896
Hey!

26:14.520 --> 26:16.399
I'm taking the girl...

26:18.081 --> 26:19.682
And you're dead.

26:31.627 --> 26:33.248
I owe you one.

26:33.909 --> 26:36.861
- Two by my count.
- Two?

26:37.150 --> 26:40.107
Ramadi, '06.

26:40.282 --> 26:43.199
- I had that guy.
- The hell you did.

26:44.865 --> 26:46.737
Give me a hand.

26:51.017 --> 26:52.813
We need to get to the truck.

26:52.913 --> 26:54.524
Okay. Come on!

27:02.764 --> 27:05.443
Keep your head down and keep swinging.

27:05.593 --> 27:10.028
Wait. We can't just go charging
out there like Leroy Jenkins.

27:10.028 --> 27:11.496
We need a plan.

27:11.521 --> 27:13.084
Leroy who?

27:13.402 --> 27:14.303
It doesn't matter.

27:14.328 --> 27:16.336
If they know where we are,
they'll be waiting for us.

27:16.336 --> 27:17.737
Then we'll just go through them.

27:17.737 --> 27:21.082
I'm sure you're probably like the
baddest guys at the bar and all...

27:21.107 --> 27:24.026
But they have guns.
We have a hammer.

27:24.026 --> 27:27.294
Look, the longer we sit here,
the more them they're gonna be.

27:27.316 --> 27:29.617
We either keep moving or we die.

27:29.617 --> 27:31.022
I'm not going out there.

27:31.062 --> 27:34.298
He's right. We gotta keep moving,
it's the only way.

27:34.323 --> 27:36.547
[KEEP LOOKING.
NEXT ROOM]

27:40.496 --> 27:42.204
Maybe it's not.

27:53.242 --> 27:55.139
- Where does this lead?
- The grain room.

27:55.139 --> 27:58.345
Lock it down. No one in, no one out. Go!

27:58.517 --> 28:00.552
Get the guys!

28:01.612 --> 28:04.513
[BLOCK THIS BREWERY DOWN]

28:09.757 --> 28:12.251
[NEXT STOREY DOWN]

28:12.549 --> 28:14.089
[COPY THAT]

28:14.575 --> 28:17.111
[INDISTINCT YELLING]

28:17.798 --> 28:19.883
[LET'S GO]

28:19.908 --> 28:21.930
[TWO SECURE]

28:29.109 --> 28:30.541
Come on.

28:40.222 --> 28:41.509
We're running out of time.

28:41.509 --> 28:43.392
Grain room is this way. No way to go.

28:43.392 --> 28:45.066
Luke, hurry!

28:51.033 --> 28:53.539
Ready or not, soldier boys!

29:10.026 --> 29:12.740
- How far down?
- Far.

29:13.538 --> 29:15.150
Do you know where it lets out?

29:16.326 --> 29:18.558
There's only one way to find out.

29:18.583 --> 29:20.294
[LAST CHANCE, MARINES]

29:25.571 --> 29:27.391
[WHAT'S IT GONNA BE, HUH?]

29:27.416 --> 29:29.675
[EASY WAY?
OR THE HARD WAY?]

29:32.541 --> 29:36.296
There's about ten feet
diagonal fall by a long drop.

29:36.374 --> 29:39.225
Keep yourself waxed. Take it slowly.

29:39.250 --> 29:40.946
[COME ON, OPEN UP]

29:43.342 --> 29:46.036
Get in there! Come on, come on!

29:47.609 --> 29:50.276
All right, come one.
You're up. Let's go.

29:50.301 --> 29:51.666
Yup.

29:56.836 --> 29:58.536
Take it easy.

29:58.561 --> 30:00.366
You can do it.

30:10.808 --> 30:12.361
You can do it, Sarah.

30:21.690 --> 30:24.460
Easy, easy, Sarah.

30:25.662 --> 30:27.163
You're doing great.

30:27.608 --> 30:29.246
Slowly.

30:29.271 --> 30:31.048
Just go.

30:32.032 --> 30:33.747
You're doing great, Sarah.

30:37.005 --> 30:38.588
We have to hurry!

30:39.055 --> 30:42.580
Not too fast.
Keep pressing to the sides.

30:53.588 --> 30:55.786
Sarah, you can do this.

31:00.162 --> 31:03.031
Be calm. Nice and slow.

31:03.385 --> 31:06.054
[SCREAMS FRANTICALLY]

31:06.264 --> 31:08.089
Oh, shit!

31:09.692 --> 31:11.330
Jake?

31:11.971 --> 31:16.086
[BOTH SCREAM]

31:16.246 --> 31:17.570
Jake!

31:17.914 --> 31:19.439
Jake!

31:21.183 --> 31:22.269
Jake?

31:23.885 --> 31:26.036
We're good!

31:28.515 --> 31:30.347
I slipped.

31:30.678 --> 31:32.143
You think?

31:32.160 --> 31:33.686
Sorry.

31:47.527 --> 31:50.471
[WHISTLES TAUNTINGLY]

32:03.725 --> 32:05.148
Get up, man.

32:23.953 --> 32:27.640
Hey, Leatherneck! Catch!

32:27.767 --> 32:29.041
Oh, shit!

32:34.752 --> 32:36.380
Let's go, let's go!

33:12.248 --> 33:14.235
Luke! You're all right?

33:16.052 --> 33:18.289
Nope. Not at all.

33:21.049 --> 33:23.216
- Is it deep?
- Yeah.

33:23.810 --> 33:26.037
- You should've caught me.
- I didn't have enough time.

33:26.037 --> 33:27.435
You caught her.

33:28.504 --> 33:29.886
Oh, Jeez!

33:29.886 --> 33:32.620
Leave that be. Luke?
It's better where it is.

33:32.620 --> 33:34.539
It's easy for you to say.

33:36.825 --> 33:39.610
- Yeah, I really wouldn't do that.
- Don't!

33:39.635 --> 33:42.262
[SCREAMS IN PAIN]

33:42.287 --> 33:43.808
I think I'm gonna throw up.

33:45.217 --> 33:47.815
You're a stubborn son of a bitch,
you know that?

33:49.817 --> 33:52.829
Could you hand me that?
I'm gonna try to stop the bleeding.

34:02.418 --> 34:06.478
[HEY, SOLDIER BOYS!
WE'RE COMING FOR YOU!]

34:10.146 --> 34:12.147
I'm gonna kill that guy.

34:43.862 --> 34:45.429
It's that way.

34:51.951 --> 34:53.781
Oh, shoot.

35:00.922 --> 35:03.270
All right, look.
It's not that bad.

35:03.933 --> 35:05.362
Yo!

35:08.873 --> 35:11.854
- I thought you finished that guy.
- So did I.

35:12.129 --> 35:14.738
Look, just give us the girl
and you two can walk away.

35:14.763 --> 35:15.825
That's not gonna happen.

35:15.825 --> 35:17.586
You just met her.
You can't be that attached.

35:17.586 --> 35:19.175
I guess we're gonna find out.

35:19.287 --> 35:20.792
Round two.

35:21.130 --> 35:24.327
I get this one.
You get beef kick over there.

36:17.683 --> 36:18.951
No!

36:19.843 --> 36:21.486
Get off!

36:52.335 --> 36:55.566
Stop screaming!

37:08.404 --> 37:10.822
- I got three.
- So did I.

37:10.847 --> 37:13.085
- I got the big one.
- Horse shit!

37:13.085 --> 37:15.228
This guy had a cattle prod.

37:15.997 --> 37:16.997
Look.

37:22.911 --> 37:24.511
Thanks, Graham.

37:24.536 --> 37:26.092
Come on.

37:27.927 --> 37:29.902
This way.

37:40.552 --> 37:43.418
- It's chain shot.
- Let the big bull charge.

37:43.418 --> 37:45.217
You shouldn't be setting
that shoulder on anything.

37:45.242 --> 37:46.599
Whoa, whoa!

37:46.697 --> 37:49.060
Why don't you let me worry about that?

37:49.073 --> 37:51.009
We need to stop the bleeding.

37:51.585 --> 37:54.013
Well, buddy, why don't you
drop me by the old case back

37:54.013 --> 37:56.005
on the way out here?

37:58.457 --> 38:00.475
Are you guys serious?

38:09.538 --> 38:12.124
I thought the thing wasn't loaded.

38:12.528 --> 38:14.220
It is now.

38:14.280 --> 38:16.227
We need your help.

38:16.423 --> 38:18.477
Funny how that works.

38:18.502 --> 38:19.972
Please.

38:26.967 --> 38:28.929
All right. Come on, now.

38:37.589 --> 38:41.165
Maddy and her brother kicked
everyone out of here last week.

38:41.190 --> 38:42.823
And they just let you stay?

38:42.823 --> 38:45.392
Yeah, I guess I'm one stubborn S.O.B.

38:45.392 --> 38:46.849
God!

38:46.887 --> 38:49.545
- You're telling me?
- Do you have a first aid kit?

38:49.545 --> 38:51.945
I need gauze, disinfectant,
whatever you got.

38:51.945 --> 38:54.378
Son, I don't even got electricity.

38:54.416 --> 38:57.571
- Where do you...?
- Hey, don't touch my stuff!

38:58.542 --> 39:01.605
Seriously, though...
where did you find all this?

39:01.634 --> 39:04.092
Goodwill, garbage cans, dumpsters...

39:04.112 --> 39:05.796
Oh, why'd you save it all?

39:05.814 --> 39:08.640
Well, it don't seem right,
throwing it all away.

39:08.665 --> 39:10.692
People died for that flag.

39:15.188 --> 39:16.488
How does it look?

39:16.488 --> 39:18.416
Around your neck it's thoracic.

39:19.037 --> 39:21.661
There's too much blood.
I can't be sure.

39:21.743 --> 39:22.808
You need a hospital.

39:22.808 --> 39:25.671
- That isn't an option.
- Luke, I'm serious.

39:25.741 --> 39:28.702
This is bad. For once in your life,
just listen to me.

39:28.727 --> 39:30.087
You could bleed out.

39:30.138 --> 39:32.047
Remember Helmand, '09?

39:32.047 --> 39:36.036
No more stories, Luke.
We don't have time. I gotta think.

39:36.862 --> 39:40.655
We got cut off. Pinned down.
They said no one goes out.

39:40.931 --> 39:44.003
- Slick Willy, he took one on the gut.
- Yeah, I remember.

39:44.847 --> 39:46.483
It was something, huh?

39:48.050 --> 39:49.612
Field cook?

39:50.073 --> 39:51.516
Bingo.

39:52.042 --> 39:53.837
Have you a spare round?

40:05.185 --> 40:08.419
Man, just dump the whole thing in there.
I want to do this twice.

40:08.444 --> 40:10.354
I'm trying to minimize the damage.

40:10.455 --> 40:12.613
So, this actually works?

40:12.861 --> 40:14.276
Sometimes.

40:14.446 --> 40:17.882
- And is it safe?
- Oh, I didn't say that.

40:17.930 --> 40:19.972
How are you two still alive?

40:20.033 --> 40:21.681
Good question.

40:21.706 --> 40:23.290
For the pain.

40:26.015 --> 40:28.297
I don't like to drink alone.

40:28.383 --> 40:30.876
You're not gonna ask me twice.

40:38.183 --> 40:39.824
To Robbie.

40:41.154 --> 40:44.351
Yeah, all right. To Robbie.

40:50.810 --> 40:54.164
All right, light me up, Doc.

41:02.534 --> 41:04.890
Are you ready for this?

41:04.915 --> 41:08.009
No, but do it anyway.

41:16.843 --> 41:18.825
We'll find them, Maddy.

41:20.038 --> 41:21.634
Excuse me?

41:22.264 --> 41:25.682
I said we'll find them.
Make them pay.

41:27.278 --> 41:31.349
But, you've already found them...

41:31.796 --> 41:34.315
Twice by my count.

41:35.964 --> 41:38.549
You told us not to use guns.

41:39.552 --> 41:41.758
I did say that, didn't I?

41:41.783 --> 41:44.630
We could've stopped this, we could...

41:46.269 --> 41:48.170
You shouldn't need guns.

41:48.170 --> 41:50.389
Maddy, wait, wait...

41:59.260 --> 42:01.322
And where were you?

42:02.384 --> 42:04.659
Securing the exits.

42:05.293 --> 42:06.234
Like you asked.

42:06.251 --> 42:07.759
- And they got out.
- They didn't.

42:07.759 --> 42:10.169
Then, where are they?

42:19.739 --> 42:22.350
Just make sure you have a clear shot.

42:22.375 --> 42:25.141
I wouldn't want you
to end up like Rooney.

42:26.153 --> 42:27.507
I'll kill them myself.

42:27.507 --> 42:28.818
She lives. They die.

42:28.850 --> 42:30.559
- Yeah.
- Good.

42:30.584 --> 42:32.222
Get in here.

42:38.496 --> 42:40.324
What are you looking at?

42:50.320 --> 42:51.812
I told you it'd work.

42:51.866 --> 42:53.812
You'll need antibiotics
when we get out of here.

42:53.837 --> 42:55.994
I still got a couple left
over from that ear infection.

42:56.010 --> 42:57.882
- I'll take them when I get home.
- No.

42:57.944 --> 43:00.442
You need a real doctor, real medicine.

43:00.613 --> 43:02.351
Just promise me you'll to hospital.

43:02.383 --> 43:04.599
- All right. Relax.
- And now, we're even.

43:04.624 --> 43:07.387
Whoa, whoa! This takes care
of saving your life upstairs.

43:07.412 --> 43:10.294
You still owe me for these two.

43:11.691 --> 43:13.492
How could I forget?

43:13.669 --> 43:16.126
Now, could you put something
on so we can get out of here?

43:16.151 --> 43:19.274
Well, this is all I got.

43:24.473 --> 43:26.657
Oh, nice T-shirt, grandma.

43:31.467 --> 43:33.269
Don't let me die in this thing.

43:33.501 --> 43:35.407
We're not dying in here.

43:36.809 --> 43:39.999
Is there a back way out of this place?
Something that they don't know about?

43:40.088 --> 43:42.835
There are some old tunnels.
They lead the docks.

43:42.835 --> 43:44.014
Where's the entrance?

43:44.014 --> 43:46.160
There's a dead phone in the loading bay.

43:46.185 --> 43:49.380
But I don't know what
shape the tunnels are in.

43:49.439 --> 43:50.886
What do you think?

43:50.898 --> 43:52.708
Better than staying in here.

43:52.737 --> 43:54.101
Can you take us there?

43:54.126 --> 43:56.615
One more patrolling
ain't gonna hurt me.

43:57.542 --> 43:59.666
Let's just hope this doesn't
turn into a combat mission.

43:59.666 --> 44:01.487
We'll need this.

44:04.257 --> 44:05.433
Now...

44:06.180 --> 44:07.719
Attention!

44:08.316 --> 44:10.153
Fall in, men.

44:24.932 --> 44:26.348
Stay together.

44:26.443 --> 44:28.136
Keep close.

44:38.412 --> 44:40.057
Hey, Tommy.

44:40.116 --> 44:42.794
How come you never let me
get you out of that place? Huh?

44:42.819 --> 44:46.240
I made my own bed.
I'm man enough to light it.

44:46.265 --> 44:48.620
You're even more stubborn than I am.

44:53.967 --> 44:55.540
Hey.

44:56.197 --> 44:57.897
Look, guys, take the old man's room.

44:57.897 --> 45:00.878
- You... stay with me.
- I don't see 'em.

45:05.863 --> 45:07.398
[GUYS]

45:07.728 --> 45:09.442
[IT'S ALL CLEAR]

45:13.047 --> 45:14.931
Wait.

45:15.335 --> 45:17.264
Shhhhhh...

45:28.226 --> 45:29.888
[RAT SQUEAKING]

45:29.888 --> 45:31.386
[SARAH SCARES]

45:33.157 --> 45:36.245
[METALLIC SOUND]

45:38.762 --> 45:41.211
Maybe they didn't hear us.

45:43.683 --> 45:45.838
[CAN MAKES NOISE ON FLOOR]

45:46.547 --> 45:47.886
Run!

45:52.655 --> 45:54.775
Don't hit the girl!

46:09.237 --> 46:11.173
Get this off me!

46:23.986 --> 46:25.500
Over here!

46:27.421 --> 46:28.887
Luke, come on!

46:28.912 --> 46:31.909
We got 'em on out tail.
I'm just gonna slow them down a bit.

46:34.877 --> 46:37.776
We got a problem.
That's the entrance to the tunnels.

46:37.776 --> 46:38.732
Don't tell me that.

46:38.732 --> 46:42.110
- The car's right on top of it.
- Of course it is.

46:42.236 --> 46:43.241
Put it in neutral.

46:43.266 --> 46:45.237
- Get up!
- Go, move it!

46:45.262 --> 46:46.796
Go!

46:50.077 --> 46:51.799
Are you up for this, old man?

46:51.824 --> 46:54.044
Shut up and push.

47:00.311 --> 47:02.122
In-coming!

47:08.663 --> 47:10.653
- Is it in neutral?
- I don't know!

47:10.665 --> 47:13.319
- What do you mean "You don't know?"
- I drive a Prius!

47:14.206 --> 47:16.630
I'm gonna die in this shirt.

47:17.138 --> 47:18.447
Take the clutch!

47:18.454 --> 47:20.971
- Which one is it?
- The left one!

47:39.293 --> 47:40.772
Sarah, get out. Let's go!

47:40.828 --> 47:42.579
At the side, at the side!

47:42.596 --> 47:45.708
- A little help over here!
- Working on it!

47:47.258 --> 47:48.648
I got it.

48:16.988 --> 48:18.451
Keep your head down.

48:18.738 --> 48:19.930
She made it.

48:20.031 --> 48:22.277
Get ready to move!

48:24.350 --> 48:25.944
Now!

48:41.817 --> 48:43.767
How many are there?

48:44.259 --> 48:45.673
Two!

48:49.451 --> 48:50.989
No, five!

48:51.365 --> 48:53.193
Where are you going?

49:04.111 --> 49:05.675
I got one left!

49:07.416 --> 49:08.971
I'm out!

49:09.550 --> 49:11.258
Move forward!

49:14.388 --> 49:15.700
Luke!

49:22.239 --> 49:24.446
Run!

49:30.972 --> 49:33.015
Please, work!

50:02.947 --> 50:05.264
- Did you see that?
- It's hard to miss.

50:05.368 --> 50:07.325
Tommy!

50:11.278 --> 50:13.076
Okay...

50:13.507 --> 50:16.025
Tommy, come here. Come.

50:16.666 --> 50:19.573
[SCREAMS IN PAIN]

50:19.791 --> 50:22.224
Hang in there, buddy.
Hang on, okay?

50:22.623 --> 50:25.346
You're gonna be all right.
Just keep breathing.

50:25.693 --> 50:27.710
Don't lie to me, kid.

50:28.736 --> 50:30.705
I know a kill shot when I see it.

50:30.705 --> 50:32.312
Come on.
I've seen worse.

50:32.312 --> 50:34.261
Yeah, I'm a dead man.

50:34.713 --> 50:36.580
We just need you to get you out of here.

50:36.637 --> 50:37.638
No.

50:37.674 --> 50:39.045
No, no...

50:39.070 --> 50:41.076
I'm fine right here.

50:41.349 --> 50:43.505
Wait, wait, wait...

50:44.098 --> 50:46.519
Take this for me.

50:46.730 --> 50:48.570
It was Robbie's.

50:49.984 --> 50:51.473
Now...

50:52.465 --> 50:55.386
Finish your mission, Marine.

50:56.637 --> 50:58.718
Semper fi.

51:18.871 --> 51:20.504
Grab a gun.

51:20.606 --> 51:22.642
Let's finish this.

51:56.555 --> 51:58.406
They're in the tunnels.

51:58.477 --> 52:00.536
Those tunnels lead to the docks.

52:00.754 --> 52:02.567
Call Kat, make sure
she's waiting for them.

52:02.590 --> 52:05.053
You get down there and drive them to us.

52:05.303 --> 52:08.131
- What are you gonna do?
- What you couldn't.

52:27.915 --> 52:30.347
This trial's been going on for 13 days.

52:30.347 --> 52:32.768
- Man, I wanna go home.
- Yeah, so do I.

52:32.793 --> 52:34.714
Then, repeat after me: "Guilty."

52:34.714 --> 52:37.749
Look, I'm sorry.
I just don't see it that way, okay?

52:37.773 --> 52:40.067
They killed cops, Patrick.

52:40.092 --> 52:41.584
- Cops.
- Allegedly.

52:41.584 --> 52:42.614
No, not allegedly.

52:42.614 --> 52:45.016
It's right there in black and white.
Look!

52:45.099 --> 52:47.181
You have a daughter, right?

52:47.458 --> 52:50.288
You don't want this monster
on the street with her...

52:50.738 --> 52:52.334
Do you?

52:54.942 --> 52:56.937
No, I don't.

53:01.661 --> 53:03.989
But you have my vote.

53:05.333 --> 53:08.201
And I'm not gonna change my mind.

53:19.742 --> 53:24.742
Translation and subtitles by
PEPPER & LALASPAIN
*** SONG LIVES FOR EVER ***

53:38.018 --> 53:40.526
So, what do they call
these things again?

53:40.587 --> 53:42.210
Shanghai tunnels.

53:42.256 --> 53:45.872
Downtown is littered with them.
I didn't think they ran way out here.

53:45.899 --> 53:48.376
I'm surprised they haven't
filled them in by now.

53:48.529 --> 53:50.065
They're a big deal.

53:50.164 --> 53:52.276
I did a paper on them
for my EP Lit class.

53:52.276 --> 53:54.310
They used to do tours and stuff.

53:54.335 --> 53:56.679
Oh, great. Maybe we'll run in a
tour group while we're down here.

53:56.679 --> 53:58.214
They can schlep us out of here.

53:58.239 --> 54:00.410
Oh, no, I don't think so.

54:00.435 --> 54:01.836
Why is that?

54:01.909 --> 54:04.991
Oh, well, two years ago a tunnel
collapsed on a tour group

54:05.012 --> 54:06.913
Killed three people, so...

54:06.938 --> 54:09.574
They don't run them anymore.
It's just too dangerous.

54:09.599 --> 54:10.906
Hey, do us a favor...

54:10.906 --> 54:14.123
Keep that shit to yourself
until we get out of here, huh?

54:14.242 --> 54:16.790
Yeah, yeah, sure. Sorry.

54:16.815 --> 54:18.581
[RATS SQUEAKING]

54:50.023 --> 54:52.505
<i>- What's up, Kat?</i>
- Yeah, we're in.

54:52.505 --> 54:54.280
<i>We're gonna chase them for you.
You got this?</i>

54:54.294 --> 54:56.367
Don't worry about it, sweetheart.

54:56.392 --> 54:58.927
I'll bury those boys down here.

55:07.879 --> 55:09.552
Let's go.

55:24.772 --> 55:26.768
Another dead end.

55:38.259 --> 55:39.898
What do you think?

55:40.322 --> 55:43.231
Eenie, Meenie, Miney, mo...

55:43.725 --> 55:45.719
Better than the thing I got.

55:45.744 --> 55:47.652
Hey, shut off your lights for a second?

55:47.681 --> 55:49.415
Why would we do that?

55:49.449 --> 55:50.884
Because if it's dark enough,

55:50.909 --> 55:52.707
maybe we'll see daylight and you know,

55:52.732 --> 55:54.151
find our way out of here?

55:54.154 --> 55:55.515
Worth a shot.

55:55.515 --> 55:57.593
Look, the last time I listened to her,

55:57.618 --> 55:59.470
I got hit in the head,
fell down a grain chute,

55:59.470 --> 56:01.603
and then impaled on a steel rod.

56:05.206 --> 56:06.997
[WHISTLING TAUNTINGLY]

56:07.034 --> 56:08.882
Looks like they already found us.

56:08.882 --> 56:10.991
No, they know we're down here,

56:11.016 --> 56:12.949
but they don't know where we are.

56:13.006 --> 56:15.159
They must have heard us
or saw our flash lights.

56:15.159 --> 56:17.988
No, if they saw us,
we'd be dead already.

56:18.126 --> 56:19.596
Hey...

56:21.785 --> 56:24.882
- See? I told you!
- Sarah!

56:25.062 --> 56:27.520
That ain't daylight, kid.

56:28.440 --> 56:30.120
Come on!

56:30.145 --> 56:32.477
- Whoa! Whoa!
- Back up!

56:32.802 --> 56:35.375
Chill out, man. Chill out.

56:35.429 --> 56:37.697
She might be one of them.

56:39.028 --> 56:40.896
One of what?

56:40.921 --> 56:42.434
No, no, come on,

56:42.459 --> 56:45.415
- She ran into me. I didn't touch her.
- Shhhh!

56:45.547 --> 56:47.149
What are you doing down here?

56:47.174 --> 56:48.903
We were squatting upstairs.
We got kicked out.

56:48.928 --> 56:50.323
I've been living
down here ever since.

56:50.344 --> 56:52.680
And you just wander
the tunnels by yourself?

56:52.680 --> 56:56.378
I heard an explosion.
I came to check it out. That's all.

56:56.441 --> 56:59.038
- Could you lower that thing?
- Not yet.

56:59.063 --> 57:02.042
- You have a phone?
- No.

57:03.522 --> 57:05.928
I don't know you are
but right now I don't care.

57:05.953 --> 57:07.541
But you're gonna lead us out of here.

57:07.566 --> 57:10.234
- Can you do that?
- Yeah.

57:10.318 --> 57:12.555
Come on.
It's this way.

57:16.309 --> 57:18.306
You really think
she looks like a squatter?

57:18.306 --> 57:19.517
I didn't say that.

57:19.517 --> 57:20.846
But it's either her or those guys.

57:20.846 --> 57:22.321
She's not the one shooting at us.

57:22.321 --> 57:25.180
- Yet.
- Just keep your eyes open.

57:46.996 --> 57:48.860
This way.

58:07.691 --> 58:09.289
How much further?

58:09.289 --> 58:11.746
Not much. I promise.

58:11.807 --> 58:14.159
So, you live down here by yourself?

58:14.195 --> 58:17.055
No, just me and a couple friends.

58:17.080 --> 58:19.357
Uh-huh. What's your name?

58:19.382 --> 58:21.178
- Kat.
- Kat.

58:21.178 --> 58:23.572
How come you and your friends
didn't move to another building

58:23.597 --> 58:25.922
instead of living
down here like rats?

58:26.162 --> 58:30.093
We like our privacy.
Nobody bothers us down here.

58:30.514 --> 58:32.490
Uh-huh...

58:43.867 --> 58:45.870
Almost there.

58:45.932 --> 58:48.683
[PHONE RINGS]

58:51.147 --> 58:53.580
I thought you didn't have a phone.

58:53.996 --> 58:57.484
Yeah, I was lying about that, actually.

58:57.537 --> 58:59.445
What else are you lying about?

59:02.799 --> 59:06.662
Well, this isn't the way out, for one.

59:06.662 --> 59:09.060
- I knew we couldn't trust her.
- Yeah.

59:10.162 --> 59:11.582
Hey, boys!

59:11.607 --> 59:13.070
Get down!

01:00:31.780 --> 01:00:33.247
No!

01:00:34.751 --> 01:00:36.732
Sarah!

01:00:37.050 --> 01:00:39.045
Don't worry, sweetie.

01:00:39.070 --> 01:00:41.721
We're gonna shoot her in the head
and then dump her body in the harbor.

01:00:41.721 --> 01:00:43.584
It'll be painless.

01:01:03.912 --> 01:01:05.586
Are you good?

01:01:18.945 --> 01:01:20.585
What are you gonna do
with that, jarhead?

01:01:20.614 --> 01:01:22.153
Improvise.

01:01:26.830 --> 01:01:28.549
Adapt.

01:01:36.389 --> 01:01:38.037
Overcome.

01:01:55.352 --> 01:01:57.071
They got Sarah.

01:01:57.618 --> 01:01:59.625
Not for long.

01:02:23.521 --> 01:02:25.426
I feel a breeze.

01:02:28.718 --> 01:02:30.049
Clear!

01:02:30.150 --> 01:02:32.043
We got an exit.

01:02:32.552 --> 01:02:34.135
Go! Go!

01:02:34.224 --> 01:02:36.207
Hey! I got them!

01:02:37.091 --> 01:02:38.573
Shit!

01:02:40.939 --> 01:02:43.234
We found you!

01:02:43.259 --> 01:02:46.533
- I thought you said it was clear!
- It was!

01:03:05.113 --> 01:03:08.576
Well, looks like we're not
gonna make it for tip-off.

01:03:08.601 --> 01:03:10.270
Never were.

01:03:10.477 --> 01:03:13.017
Hell, I don't even like basketball.

01:03:13.017 --> 01:03:16.216
I just bought those tickets to get
you into coming out with me today.

01:03:16.241 --> 01:03:17.659
You could've just asked me.

01:03:25.737 --> 01:03:27.582
I hate owing people favors!

01:03:27.582 --> 01:03:29.976
- [WE GOT THEM PINNED]
- We'll call it even.

01:03:30.001 --> 01:03:30.846
Yeah.

01:03:30.846 --> 01:03:33.358
- [DON'T WASTE YOUR AMMO]
- I don't like being owed.

01:03:36.842 --> 01:03:38.122
Shit!

01:03:42.270 --> 01:03:44.199
I can't believe it.

01:03:45.859 --> 01:03:50.146
After six tours, I'm gonna die
in a tunnel with another man's rifle.

01:03:50.163 --> 01:03:53.192
[COME ON OUT, GUYS.
WE GOT YOU SURROUNDED]

01:04:01.708 --> 01:04:02.967
Hey.

01:04:03.042 --> 01:04:05.142
Remember Kunjak?

01:04:05.774 --> 01:04:07.989
You're telling stories now?

01:04:08.281 --> 01:04:10.469
I thought that was my thing.

01:04:10.613 --> 01:04:14.329
You took two bullets in the gut
covering my retreat.

01:04:14.497 --> 01:04:16.342
I was your C.O.

01:04:19.489 --> 01:04:23.472
My job was to keep you alive.
That was a tactical retreat.

01:04:25.361 --> 01:04:27.124
Exactly.

01:04:38.928 --> 01:04:40.838
Jesus, Jake.

01:04:43.047 --> 01:04:44.503
[I THINK THEY'RE OUT!]

01:04:44.503 --> 01:04:46.103
[GO GET THEM]

01:04:47.668 --> 01:04:50.104
[THEY'RE STILL HERE.
GET UP!]

01:04:50.129 --> 01:04:51.637
Are you all right?

01:05:10.903 --> 01:05:12.704
Get Sarah.

01:05:13.483 --> 01:05:15.475
Finish this.

01:05:16.131 --> 01:05:17.943
Don't do it, Jake.

01:05:17.968 --> 01:05:19.566
Don't you do it!

01:05:19.591 --> 01:05:21.459
We're even.

01:05:25.144 --> 01:05:26.723
No!

01:06:44.763 --> 01:06:47.704
No! Jake!

01:06:48.069 --> 01:06:49.994
No!

01:07:17.447 --> 01:07:19.439
Good-bye, Marine.

01:07:33.853 --> 01:07:36.090
[JAKE!]

01:07:40.640 --> 01:07:43.579
[SHOTS FIRED]

01:07:45.104 --> 01:07:47.347
- Where does that come out?
- No idea.

01:07:47.372 --> 01:07:48.965
You two, find him!

01:07:48.990 --> 01:07:51.298
- What about me?
- We got a boat to catch.

01:07:51.453 --> 01:07:53.087
You didn't have to kill him!

01:07:53.106 --> 01:07:56.528
Luke's not gonna let you get away
with this. He's gonna find you!

01:07:56.528 --> 01:07:58.916
Then I'll put him in the ground too.

01:08:32.167 --> 01:08:33.767
Sarah...

01:08:35.225 --> 01:08:37.303
If this dude's got a brain,

01:08:37.303 --> 01:08:39.381
he's halfway to Portland by now.

01:08:39.448 --> 01:08:42.406
It's a waste of time.
Let's get to the boat.

01:08:42.475 --> 01:08:43.846
[PSSST]

01:09:17.946 --> 01:09:19.500
Here, take her.

01:09:19.600 --> 01:09:21.095
Let's go.

01:09:40.841 --> 01:09:43.654
I wonder how the trial's going.

01:09:44.459 --> 01:09:46.390
Now, will you look at that?

01:09:46.415 --> 01:09:49.725
"Hung Jury. Judge declares
mistrial on all counts.

01:09:49.751 --> 01:09:51.604
Horace Hayes to walk."

01:09:52.361 --> 01:09:55.597
Looks like your Daddy pulled
through for you after all.

01:09:55.697 --> 01:09:57.363
Then let me go.

01:09:57.388 --> 01:10:00.032
We did what you ask.
We won't tell anyone, please.

01:10:00.057 --> 01:10:03.171
Oh, sweetheart, you should know
me better than that by now.

01:10:03.196 --> 01:10:05.622
You're a loose end and so is your Daddy.

01:10:06.859 --> 01:10:08.614
Bitch.

01:10:11.200 --> 01:10:14.489
- Take her on board.
- My pleasure.

01:10:18.490 --> 01:10:20.112
Kill him!

01:10:21.147 --> 01:10:22.939
Hey! Hey!

01:10:24.036 --> 01:10:25.966
Get off me!

01:10:27.360 --> 01:10:28.780
- What's going on?
- Go, go, go!

01:10:28.780 --> 01:10:30.957
- What about the others?
- Now!

01:11:13.168 --> 01:11:14.705
Luke!

01:12:05.906 --> 01:12:07.372
Nice shirt.

01:12:08.937 --> 01:12:11.963
Did you happen to bring
my knife by any chance?

01:12:13.040 --> 01:12:14.422
No.

01:12:16.948 --> 01:12:18.922
But I know where you left it.

01:12:18.947 --> 01:12:22.198
Oh, I owe you better, sweetheart.
He can keep it.

01:12:33.619 --> 01:12:35.224
So, was that your plan?

01:12:35.249 --> 01:12:38.594
Jump on the boat and beat the poor
little woman into submission, huh?

01:12:38.687 --> 01:12:42.902
Honestly, I'm just kind
of making this up as I go.

01:12:56.247 --> 01:12:59.061
Oh, I expected more from you.

01:13:07.879 --> 01:13:10.083
This is a fight you can't win, Marine.

01:13:10.619 --> 01:13:14.214
I've never really been good at losing.

01:13:17.829 --> 01:13:20.102
Oh, what are you gonna do
with that, huh?

01:13:20.490 --> 01:13:24.127
Just a little something
a friend taught me.

01:13:42.242 --> 01:13:43.908
No, no, no!

01:13:43.978 --> 01:13:45.381
No!

01:15:12.735 --> 01:15:17.735
Translation and subtitles by
PEPPER & LALASPAIN
*** SONG LIVES FOR EVER ***

01:15:25.860 --> 01:15:28.647
So, end with it.
Let me get this straight.

01:15:28.661 --> 01:15:30.850
You killed all these men?

01:15:30.875 --> 01:15:32.632
More or less.

01:15:33.925 --> 01:15:36.044
But where's Miss Hayes now?

01:15:36.283 --> 01:15:38.067
At the bottom of the ocean?

01:15:38.097 --> 01:15:39.546
Are you sure?

01:15:40.247 --> 01:15:42.005
I put her there.

01:15:42.691 --> 01:15:44.538
What about Horace?

01:15:44.654 --> 01:15:46.084
Does he just walk?

01:15:46.109 --> 01:15:47.653
Oh, I wouldn't worry about that.

01:15:47.680 --> 01:15:50.055
I think they got a whole sue
of new charges for him.

01:15:50.055 --> 01:15:51.308
Sarah!

01:15:51.558 --> 01:15:52.856
Sarah?

01:15:52.937 --> 01:15:55.192
- Dad!
- I'm sorry, baby!

01:15:55.217 --> 01:15:56.797
We'll pick this up later.

01:15:56.822 --> 01:15:59.743
I'm okay, I'm fine. I'm fine.

01:15:59.821 --> 01:16:01.295
Thanks to him.

01:16:01.320 --> 01:16:03.091
Hey, thank you.

01:16:03.125 --> 01:16:05.109
Thank you.
The officers told me what you did.

01:16:05.109 --> 01:16:06.796
I don't know what we would have done.

01:16:06.821 --> 01:16:09.685
- It wasn't just me.
- Soldier coming through.

01:16:10.442 --> 01:16:13.141
Hey, give me a second?

01:16:24.684 --> 01:16:26.969
Semper fi, brother.

01:16:32.840 --> 01:16:34.778
We're even.

01:16:43.752 --> 01:16:46.091
- Just give me a second.
- Sure.

01:16:55.826 --> 01:16:57.531
How are you doing?

01:16:58.486 --> 01:17:00.702
I was gonna ask you the same thing.

01:17:02.030 --> 01:17:03.833
Just saying good-bye.

01:17:06.276 --> 01:17:08.732
I'm so sorry about Jake.

01:17:09.534 --> 01:17:12.060
You know, he'd do all again tomorrow?

01:17:13.967 --> 01:17:15.872
Even knowing the outcome.

01:17:21.285 --> 01:17:23.335
He died a Marine.

01:17:40.868 --> 01:17:43.305
I should probably go to the hospital.

01:17:44.656 --> 01:17:48.180
Yeah, I think that's
probably a good idea.

01:17:53.968 --> 01:17:55.120
Hey.

01:17:55.230 --> 01:17:58.572
Come on, we gotta
get you home, okay?

